matched_lines: > community.routeros 2.20.1 (https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.routeros/blob/stable-2/CHANGELOG.md#v2-20-1) has been released. This release marks community.routeros 2.x.y as End of Life. If you haven't done so, please upgrade to community.routeros 3.x.y. Thanks to everyone who contributed to the many 2.x.y releases!

> We would appreciated any feedback on the [Awesome Ansible list: How to make it more presentable/attractive to contribute to?](https://forum.ansible.com/t/awesome-ansible-list-how-to-make-it-more-presentable-attractive-to-contribute-to/39710) forum topic. Thanks to everyone who contributed to the projects and the list!

> community.general 10.2.0 (https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.general/blob/stable-10/CHANGELOG.md#v10-2-0), community.general 9.5.3 (https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.general/blob/stable-9/CHANGELOG.md#v9-5-3), and community.general 8.6.9 (https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.general/blob/stable-8/CHANGELOG.md#v8-6-9) have been released with new features, plugins, and modules (10.2.0 only), bugfixes, and one security fix for `community.general.keycloak_authentication` when working with Keycloak 25+. Check out the linked changelogs for more details, and many thanks to everyone who contributed to these releases!

> Ansible DevTools team shared [hi-level focus areas for developer tooling in 2025](https://forum.ansible.com/t/ansible-devtools-plans-and-collaboration-opportunities/39142) with the community. Read up to find ways we can work together!

> [Luca Berton](http://forum.ansible.com/u/lucab_it/summary) has shared a blog post with details about the [Ansible London Meetup](http://forum.ansible.com/t/ansible-london-ansible-london-monday-23rd-september-2024-2024-09-23/8178) that recently took place. In his post, titled [Ansible Community Meetup 2024: Updates, Releases, and Networking](https://www.ansiblepilot.com/articles/ansible-community-meetup-2024-updates-releases-and-networking/), Luca provides his take and an overview of the presentation from the Ansible community team at Red Hat that gave a brief update on initiatives to support contributors and foster the community. So head over to Luca's blog to read the post and catch up on what took place at the London meetup.

> community.crypto 1.9.26 has been released; this final release marks community.crypto 1.x.y as **End of Life**. Please upgrade to community.crypto 2.x.y if you haven't already done so. Thanks to everyone who contributed to community.crypto 1.x.y!

> If you are using the shared workflows from https://github.com/ansible-community/github-docs-build/ to publish dcumentation to GitHub Pages as described in https://github.com/ansible-community/github-docs-build/wiki/Getting-started-with-GitHub-Pages#enabling-pages, you need to update your workflows, since publishing will no longer work since beginning of this month. See http://forum.ansible.com/t/6796 for more information.
> * How we move common code into shared libraries

> If you use the shared workflows from ansible-community/github-docs-build/ (https://github.com/ansible-community/github-docs-build/) to publish your collection's documentation to GitHub pages, please check out https://github.com/ansible-community/github-docs-build/issues/92 respectively http://forum.ansible.com/t/6796 - GitHub changes the way how GitHub Pages can be published, and the old way (also described in the github-docs-build repo's wiki) will stop working on **June 30th**.
> * Updated platform ingress to not allow modification of the shared resources (PR #15234)

> community.general  version 6.6.9 (https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.general/blob/stable-6/CHANGELOG.md#v6-6-9) was released which is the last 6.x.y release. The 6.x.y release train is therefore now End of Life. Thanks to everyone who contributed to the 6.x.y releases!

> As mentioned in [The Bullhorn #134](http://forum.ansible.com/t/4631) we discussed the possibility to add teams / a team representative to the Ansible Community Steering Committee and started a [vote](http://forum.ansible.com/t/4492/16). The proposal has been accepted, allowing a team to become part of the SC. The team will be represented by a (possibly rotating) member of said team.

> [community.rabbitmq 1.3.0](https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.rabbitmq/blob/main/CHANGELOG.rst) has been released with bug fixes and new features, including the ability to manage users via the API. Thank you to everyone who contributed to this release!

> There are two new GitHub Actions for [building collection artifacts](https://github.com/ansible-community/github-action-build-collection) and [testing Galaxy import with a collection](https://github.com/ansible-community/github-action-test-galaxy-import). Both actions contain a shared workflow which makes using them easier; using the action directly gives you more flexibility to include it into complex workflows. The Galaxy import shared workflow can be [added rather simply to a collection](https://github.com/ansible-community/github-action-test-galaxy-import#bundled-shared-workflow).

> The shared Ansible Working Group ICS meeting file has moved [here](https://github.com/ansible-community/meetings). Please update your calendars to use this new location! See details in the project README.

> [community.libvirt 1.3.0](https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.libvirt/blob/main/CHANGELOG.rst#v1-3-0) has been released with new bugfixes and features, including `diff` mode for the `define` command as well as a new `mutate_flags` option to modify existing domains. Thank you to everyone who contributed to this release!
